`isInstanceOf` must be the equivalent of using `instanceof` operator. The problem with using the operator directly is that the negate condition is hard to read, e.g.

``` js
if ({} instanceof Error) {
    // Good
}

if (!({} instanceof Error)) {
   // Bad
}
```

Using `isInstanceOf` would prevent a possible error of negating the subject, e.g.

``` js
if (!{} instanceof Error) {
   // Unintentional condition.
}
```

`isInstanceOf` is a lot easier to read in both scenarios:

``` js
if (_.isInstanceOf({}, Error)) {

}

if (!_.isInstanceOf({}, Error)) {

}
```

